---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Hennigan's Huddle and the person behind the mic." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About Hennigan's Huddle</h1>

			<p>
				Hennigan's Huddle is a personalized daily news podcast built by Bryan Hennigan and powered by
				AI. Every episode is generated on demand — pulling the latest headlines from RSS feeds,
				writing a conversational script with Claude, and converting it to audio with text-to-speech.
				The result is a 10-minute briefing tailored to the topics that matter most.
			</p>

			<h2>About Bryan</h2>

			<p>
				Bryan is a Senior Strategic Account Manager specializing in PLM, AEC, and Civil engineering
				software. He works at the intersection of technology and construction, helping enterprise
				clients get more value from platforms like Autodesk and Graitec. Outside of work, he follows
				Detroit sports religiously — Lions, Pistons, Red Wings, and Tigers — along with Ohio State
				football and Dayton Flyers basketball.
			</p>

			<h2>About Hen Solutions LLC</h2>

			<p>
				Hen Solutions LLC is Bryan's business focused on leveraging AI and automation to build
				practical tools and solutions. Hennigan's Huddle is one of several projects exploring how
				AI can create personalized content experiences that save people time and keep them informed.
			</p>

			<h2>How the Podcast Works</h2>

			<p>
				The tech stack is straightforward: Astro 5 handles the site, Google News RSS feeds provide
				the raw stories, Claude Haiku writes the script, and Edge TTS (or ElevenLabs for a custom
				voice clone) generates the audio. Episodes are auto-published to an iTunes-compatible RSS
				feed so you can subscribe in your favorite podcast app.
			</p>

			<p>
				Want to try it? Head to the <a href="/podcast">Podcast</a> page and generate an episode.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
